# CareerBoost, local configuration only (safe to commit, no real secrets here).
#
# Privacy: data stays on the device. Optional lines below only turn on optional online features in the app bundle.
# `EXPO_PUBLIC_*` values are included when you build — keep real keys in `.env` on your machine only (never commit `.env`).
# Restart Expo after you change `.env`.

# Weather (Insights tab), leave empty to hide live weather
# 1) Create a free account at https://openweathermap.org
# 2) Copy the long access key from your account (sometimes called “default key”).
# 3) Paste it after the equals sign on the next line.
EXPO_PUBLIC_OPENWEATHER_KEY=

# Optional: home city name for the forecast (no GPS). If you skip this, the app uses London.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_OPENWEATHER_CITY=Dublin
EXPO_PUBLIC_OPENWEATHER_CITY=
